testcat-sim
===========

This is a fork of "baguette" by tddworks (https://github.com/tddworks/baguette),
licensed under the Apache License 2.0 (see LICENSE).

Changes made in this fork:
- Removed the web/serve layer: the `serve` command, the HTTP+WebSocket server
  (Infrastructure/Server), the WebSocket frame sink, the Hummingbird
  dependencies, and all of Resources/Web (including /farm). testcat renders the
  live simulator view in its own UI by consuming `testcat-sim stream`.
- Removed the upstream test target, docs, CI, and changelog tooling.
- Renamed the executable product to `testcat-sim`.
- Added a `screencast` command — continuous live MJPEG to stdout. It runs the
  existing MJPEG stream in an async command context so SimulatorKit framebuffer
  callbacks are delivered without the (removed) web-server event loop; testcat's
  live grid consumes it.

The core simulator-control and framebuffer-stream functionality is unchanged.
The names "baguette" and "tddworks" appear only to credit the origin as required
by the Apache-2.0 attribution terms.
